	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, came to this site seeking verification, did not find it, nor in any other site.  Thus I thought I would add my little tidbit, and see if others have had this occur as well.<BR>
<BR>
Was killing Ice Giants at the entrance to Permafrost, when someone trained Tundra Jack and Iceberg to Perma.<BR>
<BR>
Now, being a Dark elf (Wizard, L51), they were not about to hold a welcoming party and give thanks to clearing the area of the Giants.  Tundra ran past me, the 1st warning I had that anything was amiss.  I promtly stood up, and got slammed into from behind by Iceberg.<BR>
<BR>
Not overly concerned, I cast Immobilize (Root).  DOH!  Resisted.  K, this is hurting (I think to myself), but still not really worried.  I cast Immobilize again.  GRRR.  Resisted again.  <BR>
<BR>
Now I  am starting to get both mad and a bit nervous; My Invuln shield has now been beaten down, and I am taking  pretty decent damage.  I decide to take off with my J-Boots, and get some distance between us for anothour cast of Immobilize.    ARGH!  This stupid GREEN is both keeping up, and still chipping rather quickly away at my health.  Well, as I had Levitate on, I start heading towards hilly area/river.  I get room to cast, but by the time Iceberg gets in range, I can only JUST get it off before he is upon me.  Thus he gets a hit or two on me B4 I bolt for the next hilltop.<BR>
<BR>
Well, to keep a long story from being a novel, I try this about 5 or 6 times.  Iceberg RESISTED root EVERY time.  EVERY single time.  NEVER have I had ANYTHING resist 3 times in a row, and the amount of times I have been resisted (Much less by a GREEN CON!) twice in a row I could count on one or 2 fingers.  Seven resists in a row, and a bar and a half of health convinced me that Perma was a very inviting destination all of a sudden.<BR>
<BR>
The finish to the story is that I made it, BARELY, as Tundra was walking back out as I was running in.  Took a couple of hits from him and a couple more from Iceberg, zoned into Perma with about a quarter bar of health left.<BR>
<BR>
What I was looking for is most likely obvious at this point.  Is Iceberg unrootable like I hear some of the new creatures in Stonebrunt are?  I never recieved a msg that he was unrootable.  Was it a bug?  A freak chance of nature that my being a Pisces (If it was not for bad luck, we would have no luck at all...) catalyzed into reality?<BR>
<BR>
Anyways, if anyone with arcane battle knowledge against Iceberg happens to read this, would appreciate what occured with your encounter.  Did you get root to stick?  As a Wiz, I could not use my Snare (Bonds of Force) as it is an AE spell, and by the time Iceberg got close enough for me to start casting, he was too close for comfort that I might  well fail my 101 points of vs Magic since I would be in range of the spell.  <BR>
<BR>
Good travels and Safe hunting!<BR>
<BR>
KK<BR>
L51 Wiz<BR>
<BR>
Syntyrr<BR>
L39 Druid<BR>
<BR>
Cyntyrr<BR>
L34 Necroette<BR>
<BR>
Dvaughn<BR>
L30 Enchanter<BR>
<BR>
...and a veritable army of sub L30 characters on various servers...   &lt;8^)P
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
